ieee8021PreemptionMib.name: ieee8021PreemptionMib

revisions.description: Published as part of IEEE Std 802.1Q 2017 revision. Cross references updated and corrected.
Initial version published as part of IEEE Std 802.1Qbu.

ieee8021PreemptionMib.contactinfo: WG-URL: http://www.ieee802.org/1/ WG-EMail: STDS-802-1-L@ieee.org Contact: IEEE 802.1 Working Group Chair Postal: C/O IEEE 802.1 Working Group IEEE Standards Association 445 Hoes Lane Piscataway NJ 08854 USA E-mail: STDS-802-1-L@ieee.org
ieee8021PreemptionMib.description: The Bridge MIB module for managing devices that support the frame preemption enhancements for IEEE 802.1Q Bridges. Unless otherwise indicated, the references in this MIB module are to IEEE Std 802.1Q. Copyright (C) IEEE (2018). This version of this MIB module is part of IEEE Std 802.1Q; see the draft itself for full legal notices.

ieee8021PreemptionParameterTable.name: ieee8021PreemptionParameterTable
ieee8021PreemptionParameterTable.description: A table containing a set of frame preemption parameters, one for each priority value. All writeable objects in this table must be persistent over power up restart/reboot.

ieee8021PreemptionParameterEntry.name: ieee8021PreemptionParameterEntry
ieee8021PreemptionParameterEntry.description: A list of objects containing preemption parameters for each priority value.

ieee8021PreemptionPriority.name: ieee8021PreemptionPriority
ieee8021PreemptionPriority.description: The priority number associated with the row of the table. A row in this table is created for each priority value.

ieee8021FramePreemptionAdminStatus.name: ieee8021FramePreemptionAdminStatus
ieee8021FramePreemptionAdminStatus.description: The value of the framePreemptionAdminStatus parameter for the traffic class. The default value of the framePreemptionAdminStatus parameter is express (1). The value of this object MUST be retained across reinitializations of the management system.

ieee8021PreemptionConfigTable.name: ieee8021PreemptionConfigTable
ieee8021PreemptionConfigTable.description: A table containing a set of frame preemption parameters, one for each Port. All writeable objects in this table must be persistent over power up restart/reboot.

ieee8021PreemptionConfigEntry.name: ieee8021PreemptionConfigEntry
ieee8021PreemptionConfigEntry.description: A list of objects containing preemption parameters for each Port.

ieee8021FramePreemptionHoldAdvance.name: ieee8021FramePreemptionHoldAdvance
ieee8021FramePreemptionHoldAdvance.description: The value of the holdAdvance parameter for the Port in nanoseconds. There is no default value; the holdAdvance is a property of the underlying MAC.

ieee8021FramePreemptionReleaseAdvance.name: ieee8021FramePreemptionReleaseAdvance
ieee8021FramePreemptionReleaseAdvance.description: The value of the releaseAdvance parameter for the Port in nanoseconds. There is no default value; the releaseAdvance is a property of the underlying MAC.

ieee8021FramePreemptionActive.name: ieee8021FramePreemptionActive
ieee8021FramePreemptionActive.description: The value is active (2) when preemption is operationally active for the Port, and idle (1) otherwise.

ieee8021FramePreemptionHoldRequest.name: ieee8021FramePreemptionHoldRequest
ieee8021FramePreemptionHoldRequest.description: The value is hold (1) when the sequence of gate operations for the Port has executed a Set-And-Hold-MAC operation, and release (2) when the sequence of gate operations has executed a Set-And-Release-MAC operation. The value of this object is release (2) on system initialization.

ieee8021PreemptionGroup.name: ieee8021PreemptionGroup
ieee8021PreemptionGroup.description: Objects that allow management of frame preemption.

ieee8021PreemptionCompliance.name: ieee8021PreemptionCompliance
ieee8021PreemptionCompliance.description: The compliance statement for devices supporting frame preemption. Support of the objects defined in this MIB module also requires support of the IEEE8021-BRIDGE-MIB; the provisions of 17.3.2 apply to implementations claiming support of this MIB.
